Definition of the variable: Name(s) of the mining companies that operated the mine. The list is non-exhaustive and includes consecutive owners and co-ownerships.
Name(s) given to the mine at any point in time (Optional).
Town where the mine is located (Optional).
Province where the mine is located.
Latitude coordinate of the mine. The format is decimal degree at the precision of 6 digits or more.
Longitude coordinate of the mine. The format is decimal degree at the precision of 6 digits or more.

Label of the variable: Year of the Start of Production
Definition of the variable: Years of production at the mine after 1949. close.i variables can indicate suspension or closure of operation: no distinction is made. In the identification of the years, production years were favored over years indicating the opening of closure of the mine. The variable takes the value of "open" when the mine is still in operation as of 2022.  If the mine produced before 1949, it might be indicated under "information".

Label of the variable: Year of the Suspension of Production
Year of the Reopening of Production
Year of the Second Suspension of Production
Year of the Reopening of Production after two suspension
Year of the Third Suspension of Production

Definition of the variable: List of all the commodities produced by the mine
Individually listed commodities produced by the mine. They are listed in order of priority. This is the same as the "commodityall" variable.

Comments and information about the mine. Examples include the labor conflict/workplace accident, scale of production (small/large), whether it is a ghost town today and facts about the agency of indigenous groups.

Indication (=1 if the source is used, =0 if the source is not used) that some information for this mine is extracted from the Canadian historical mines database by the Historical Canadian mines data hub and visualization centre Accessible at https://spatialsk.maps.arcgis.com/apps/dashboards/780a4bc0aa524cc38e10a4699bc3511e (2023).

Indication (=1 if the source is used, =0 if the source is not used) that some information for this mine is extracted from the database for that specific province or territory. For full specification on the sources for each province and territory refer to: Dallaire-Fortier, C. (2024). A comprehensive historical and geolocalized database of mining activities in Canada. Scientific Data. DOI: 10.1038/s41597-024-03116-3.
Indication (=1 if the source is used, =0 if the source is not used) that some information for this mine is extracted from the external weblinks provided (link1, link2 or link3).
References for the secondary sources that have been consulted. It is often included tracking the sources of information and justify the decisions.
